\begin{frame}[fragile]{Local migration steps}

  What would an icecuber need to change locally?

  \begin{itemize}
    \item Create a github account
    \item Become a member of the github icecube group
    \item Copy ssh key to github
    \item To get combo, one now needs to run something different:

      \begin{bash}
      # old:
      svn checkout http://code.icecube.wisc.edu/svn/meta-projects/combo/trunk src

      # new:
      git clone git@github.com:IceCube-SPNO/IceTrayCombo.git src
      svn checkout https://github.com/IceCube-SPNO/IceTrayCombo.git/trunk src
      \end{bash}

      \question{Do we know how to "symlink" the \href{http://code.icecube.wisc.edu/svn/meta-projects/combo}{meta-projects/combo} folder to github?}
  \end{itemize}

  \vfill
  \tiny See also: \url{https://github.com/fiedl/icecube-git-migration/issues/9}

\end{frame}

